column2: VARDESC

The Decayed, Missing, or Filled Tooth Surfaces Index is used by a dentist or dental hygienist to determine the prevalence of coronal caries in permanent and primary teeth through an examination that records the three components. This variable records tooth code to assess the Missing Teeth (the M Component of the DMFS Index) for tooth Upper Right 2M
column17: S = Sound permanent tooth (no decay or filling on any surface)
column18: Z = Permanent tooth with surface condition
column20: K = Primary tooth with surface condition
column22: E = Missing due to dental disease (caries/periodontal disease)
column23: M = Missing due to other causes (orthodontic/traumatic or other non-disease)
column24: R = Missing due to dental disease but replaced by a fixed restoration
column25: X = Missing due to other causes but replaced by a fixed restoration
column26: P = Missing due to dental disease but replaced by a removable restoration
column27: Q = Missing due to other causes but replaced by a removable restoration
column28: J = Permanent root tip is present but no restorative replacement is present
column29: T = Permanent root tip is present but a restorative replacement is present
